summary: TL*THE CONTACT OWNS A GRACO TURBOBOOSTER BOOSTER SEAT, MODEL NUMBER 849-12NY.  THE SEAT WAS MANUFACTURED ON OCTOBER 13, 2007.  WHEN THE VEHICLE COMES TO A COMPLETE STOP, THE BOOSTER SEAT AS WELL AS THE CHILD MOVE FORWARD.  AT A SUDDEN STOP, THE CHILD WOULD BE THROWN FORWARD, WHICH COULD POTENTIALLY CAUSE WHIPLASH.  THE CONTACT NOTICED A RECALL DISCLOSED FROM A NEWS SOURCE; HOWEVER, THE MANUFACTURER STATED THAT THERE WERE NO FAILURES WITH THE SEAT.  THE PURCHASE DATE AND FAILURE TYPE WERE UNKNOWN.
